docs.abstract: China is heavily reliant on imported computer chips, despite efforts to develop its own semiconductor industry.
docs.snippet: China is heavily reliant on imported computer chips, despite efforts to develop its own semiconductor industry.
docs.lead_paragraph: BEIJING — For all of China’s efforts to become a global force in high technology rivaling the United States, it has mostly failed to produce top-flight contenders in one crucial area: the industry that gave Silicon Valley its name.

headline.main: Huawei’s U.S. Restrictions Expose a High-Tech Achilles’ Heel for China
headline.print_headline: U.S. Exposes What China Lacks: Chips

docs.abstract: The country dominates production of the rare earths used in myriad technologies, but tangled global supply chains make it hard to hit the U.S. directly.
docs.snippet: The country dominates production of the rare earths used in myriad technologies, but tangled global supply chains make it hard to hit the U.S. directly.
docs.lead_paragraph: SHANGHAI — President Xi Jinping of China strode this week through a high-ceilinged factory that makes magnets out of rare earths, minerals that are essential to global manufacturing and a sector that his country dominates. His top trade negotiator, Vice Premier Liu He, stood near.

headline.main: China’s Supply of Minerals for iPhones and Missiles Could Be a Risky Trade Weapon
headline.print_headline: Trade Wedge For China: Its Minerals

docs.abstract: Household finances are improving in a strong job market, but just six in 10 adults still could cover a surprise expense without selling something or borrowing money.
docs.snippet: Household finances are improving in a strong job market, but just six in 10 adults still could cover a surprise expense without selling something or borrowing money.
docs.lead_paragraph: Four in 10 American adults wouldn’t be able to cover an unexpected $400 expense with cash, savings or a credit-card charge that could be quickly paid off, a new Federal Reserve survey finds.

headline.main: Many Adults Would Struggle to Find $400, the Fed Finds
headline.print_headline: Many American Adults Live On Financial Edge, Fed Says

docs.abstract: Some 2.75 trillion points and miles are earned each year, with many more options on where to spend them. Airline tickets and hotel rooms may be the best choices.
docs.snippet: Some 2.75 trillion points and miles are earned each year, with many more options on where to spend them. Airline tickets and hotel rooms may be the best choices.
docs.lead_paragraph: Not all points and miles in travel rewards programs are created equal, which means that getting the best deal isn’t always obvious.

headline.main: What Is a Reward Point Worth? It Depends
headline.print_headline: Making Those Miles Go the Distance

docs.abstract: Beijing’s matched the Trump administration’s de facto delay in collecting the new tariffs, giving both sides breathing room to reach a deal.
docs.snippet: Beijing’s matched the Trump administration’s de facto delay in collecting the new tariffs, giving both sides breathing room to reach a deal.
docs.lead_paragraph: BEIJING — China moved to retaliate against the United States, announcing plans on Monday to raise tariffs on American goods ranging from beer and wine to swimsuits, shirts and liquefied natural gas.

headline.main: With Higher Tariffs, China Retaliates Against the U.S.

docs.abstract: Candice Bergen and others from the original cast came back to a show now written for the Trump era, but reviews were mixed and ratings were poor.
docs.snippet: Candice Bergen and others from the original cast came back to a show now written for the Trump era, but reviews were mixed and ratings were poor.
docs.lead_paragraph: CBS pulled the plug on “Murphy Brown” on Friday, bringing an end to the revival of a beloved sitcom that proved to be a ratings flop this television season.

headline.main: CBS Cancels ‘Murphy Brown’ Revival After One Season
headline.print_headline: Low Ratings Doom Revival of ‘Murphy Brown’

docs.abstract: Web-focused companies are increasingly competing with traditional brokerages, moving to displace agents from the process of selling a house, and now the other side.
docs.snippet: Web-focused companies are increasingly competing with traditional brokerages, moving to displace agents from the process of selling a house, and now the other side.
docs.lead_paragraph: Redfin, the Seattle-based real estate brokerage, is starting a program that lets house hunters bid on properties directly through its website. The move aims to bring online shopping to a business dominated by attending weekend open houses and driving around with agents.

headline.main: Redfin Aims to Bring E-Commerce to Home Buying
headline.print_headline: Redfin Seeks to Bring E-Commerce to Home Buying

docs.abstract: Children’s groups say the tech giant’s Echo Dot Kids device violated a federal law protecting youngsters’ online privacy. Amazon disagrees.
docs.snippet: Children’s groups say the tech giant’s Echo Dot Kids device violated a federal law protecting youngsters’ online privacy. Amazon disagrees.
docs.lead_paragraph: Amazon barreled into the children’s smart-speaker market last year with a brightly colored device called Echo Dot Kids Edition. The tech giant played up the device as a simple way for youngsters to converse with Alexa, the company’s voice-activated virtual assistant, and obtain age-appropriate apps.

headline.main: Amazon Flunks Children’s Privacy, Advocacy Groups Charge
headline.print_headline: Critics Assail Amazon Over Children’s Privacy

docs.abstract: The Sheraton Grand Phoenix is being remade into a prototype for the new face of the brand. But Marriott will have to persuade hundreds of hotel owners to go along.
docs.snippet: The Sheraton Grand Phoenix is being remade into a prototype for the new face of the brand. But Marriott will have to persuade hundreds of hotel owners to go along.
docs.lead_paragraph: Marriott International made a down payment of sorts on a sweeping overhaul of the Sheraton brand last year, buying the Sheraton Grand Phoenix for $255 million to remake it into a prototype for the new face of the brand.

headline.main: Marriott Plans to Inject Color Into ‘Beige’ Sheratons. It Won’t Be Easy.
headline.print_headline: Big Job of Brightening a Brand

docs.abstract: Talks include creating a new committee and an external assessor that would scrutinize how well the social network protects user data.
docs.snippet: Talks include creating a new committee and an external assessor that would scrutinize how well the social network protects user data.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Federal Trade Commission is negotiating a settlement with Facebook that would create new positions at the company focused on strengthening its privacy practices, according to two people with knowledge of the talks.

headline.main: Facebook Set to Create Privacy Positions as Part of F.T.C. Settlement
headline.print_headline: Facebook Set To Add Posts To Safeguard User Privacy
